{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We always report energy, time, and unit conversion constants in double","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"precision. Potential energy can sometimes have a massive absolute value","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that dwarfs the magnitude of relative values. Rigid body bulk properties","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(only accessed by the CPU) are stored in FP64 to minimize drift from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"accumulated rounding error. Everything else is in FP32. Force"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"field parameters are in single precision because we don’t know their values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a lot of certainty. In addition, cached parameters may consume a large"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"amount of memory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some internal summation algorithms temporarily employ mixed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"precision. Both the CPU code for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MM4RigidBody"},{"text":" and GPU code for the OpenMM","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Metal plugin use block summation. The majority of the compute cost happens"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on FP32, either to harness more GFLOPS and reduce register pressure","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(CPU) or provide compatibility with a specific hardware vendor (GPU). The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rounding error is capped to whatever error occurs within a block","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(~1000 elements). Outside of the block, the number is casted to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"FP64 and summed with no additional rounding error. This prevents unexpected"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"issues popping up with large systems that exceed 1000 atoms. The mantissa","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the quantity is still ~24 bits; we just prevent it from degrading to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"~16 bits."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldEnergy\/kinetic","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldEnergy\/potential"],"title":"Instance Properties"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldEnergy","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4"]]},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy"}],"symbolKind":"struct","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:3MM40A16ForceFieldEnergyV","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"MM4"}],"title":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The energy of a force field."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefieldenergy"]}],"references":{"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4/MM4ForceFieldEnergy":{"url":"\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefieldenergy","title":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldEnergy","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MM4ForceFieldEnergy","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The energy of a force field."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4/MM4ForceFieldEnergy/kinetic":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The system’s total kinetic energy, in zeptojoules."}],"title":"kinetic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"kinetic","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"}],"url":"\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefieldenergy\/kinetic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldEnergy\/kinetic"},"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4/MM4ForceFieldEnergy/potential":{"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"potential","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double"}],"title":"potential","url":"\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4forcefieldenergy\/potential","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The system’s total potential energy, in zeptojoules."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4ForceFieldEnergy\/potential"},"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Molecular Mechanics force field, version 4. The simulator used to create "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Nanosystems (1992)","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", but updated with modern ab initio parameters.","type":"text"}],"title":"MM4","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/mm4"}}}